      • SOL_CLIENT_ACKNOWLEDGE

        static final int SOL_CLIENT_ACKNOWLEDGE
        A Solace defined message acknowledgement mode. In the case of multiple consumers on a single session, this mode allows each consumer to acknowledge only those messages received by that consumer. Under this mode, each call to Message.acknowledge() only acknowledges the caller message received by the consumer.

        Specifying different acknowledge modes has no effect on the frequency that messages are acknowledged on the appliance. The JMS connection factory message reception properties "AD Window Size" and "Acknowledgement Threshold (%)" are used to make acknowledging more or less frequent. Where "AD Window Size" = 100 and "Acknowledgement Threshold (%)" = 1 is most active, and "AD Window Size" = 255 and "Acknowledgement Threshold (%)" = 75 is most lazy.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_VPN

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_VPN
        An Optional InitialContext environment property (String value - default null). The name of the Message VPN to attempt to join when connecting to the appliance. If not specified, attempt to join to the default Message VPN for the client. This parameter is only valid for sessions operating in client mode (see InitialContext environment property SOLACE_JMS_CLIENT_MODE). If specified, it must be a maximum of 32 bytes in length when encoded as UTF-8.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_COMPRESSION_LEVEL
        An Optional InitialContext environment property (Integer value - default 0). A compression level setting of 1-9 sets the ZLIB compression level to use; a setting of 0 disables compression entirely. This parameter is only valid for sessions operating in client mode (see InitialContext environment property SOLACE_JMS_CLIENT_MODE).

      • SOLACE_JMS_JNDI_CLIENT_ID

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_JNDI_CLIENT_ID
        An Optional InitialContext environment property to set the JNDI Connection Client ID used to register with the appliance running in SolOS-TR. "Client ID" is known as "Client Name" on the appliance. If specified, it must be a valid Topic name, and a maximum of 160 bytes in length when encoded as UTF-8. If not specified, an auto-generated client id is used. This should not be confused with the "client id" JNDI property that sets the Client ID for a JMS connection. A Solace JMS defined Property.

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PROTOCOL

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PROTOCOL
        Deprecated. 
        String property specifying a comma separated list of the encryption protocol(s) to use. Allowed values are "sslv3", "tlsv1", "tlsv1.1", "tlsv1.2". When specifying more than one protocol the order is not important. Note that TLSv1.1 and TLSv1.2 are supported starting with Java 7. Default "sslv3,tlsv1,tlsv1.1,tlsv1.2" This has been deprecated in favor of specifying the excluded protocols in property SupportedProperty.SOLACE_JMS_SSL_EXCLUDED_PROTOCOLS
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_EXCLUDED_PROTOCOLS

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_EXCLUDED_PROTOCOLS
        String property specifying a comma separated list of the encryption protocol(s) NOT to use. Allowed values are "sslv3", "tlsv1", "tlsv1.1", "tlsv1.2". When specifying more than one protocol the order is not important. Note that TLSv1.1 and TLSv1.2 are supported starting with Java 7. Default "" (Don't exclude any)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_VALIDATE_CERTIFICATE

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_VALIDATE_CERTIFICATE
        Boolean property when true indicates that the API should validate server certificates with certificates in the truststore. If set to false, no validation of the certificate date or common name is performed. Default True.
        See Also:

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_VALIDATE_CERTIFICATE_DATE

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_VALIDATE_CERTIFICATE_DATE
        Boolean property when true indicates that the session connection should fail when an expired certificate or a certificate not yet in effect is received. No date validation will be performed (overriding this property) if SOLACE_JMS_SSL_VALIDATE_CERTIFICATE is set to false. Default True.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_CIPHER_SUITES

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_CIPHER_SUITES
        String property specifying a comma separated list of the cipher suites to enable in order of preference. Cipher suites can be specified using their JSSE name or OpenSSL name. The following is the list of supported Cipher suites (showing the JSSE name with the OpenSSL name in brackets):
        • TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 (ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384) * Supported starting with Java 8 and requires installation of the JCE Unlimited Strength Jurisdiction Policy Files
        • TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA384 (ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA384) * Supported starting with Java 7 and requires installation of the JCE Unlimited Strength Jurisdiction Policy Files
        • TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA (ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA) * Supported starting with Java 7 and requires installation of the JCE Unlimited Strength Jurisdiction Policy Files
        • TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 (AES256-GCM-SHA384) * Supported starting with Java 8 and requires installation of the JCE Unlimited Strength Jurisdiction Policy Files
        • TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA256 (AES256-SHA256) * Supported starting with Java 7 and requires installation of the JCE Unlimited Strength Jurisdiction Policy Files
        • TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA (AES256-SHA) * Requires installation of the JCE Unlimited Strength Jurisdiction Policy Files
        • TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA (ECDHE-RSA-DES-CBC3-SHA) * Supported starting with Java 7
        • SSL_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA (DES-CBC3-SHA)
        • TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 (ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256) * Supported starting with Java 8
        • TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA256 (ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA256) * Supported starting with Java 7
        • TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA (ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA) * Supported starting with Java 7
        • TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 (AES128-GCM-SHA256) * Supported starting with Java 8
        • TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA256 (AES128-SHA256) * Supported starting with Java 7
        • TLS_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA (AES128-SHA)
        • SSL_RSA_WITH_RC4_128_SHA (RC4-SHA)
        • SSL_RSA_WITH_RC4_128_MD5 (RC4-MD5)

        Default is all the supported ciphers.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_KEY_STORE_PASSWORD

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_KEY_STORE_PASSWORD
        This property is used to specify the password of the keystore specified by SOLACE_JMS_SSL_KEY_STORE. The keystore password allows JMS to ensure the keystore hasn't been tampered with by any party that doesn't know the keystore password. The keystore password is also used to decipher the private key if the SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD property is not specified.

        When SOLACE_JMS_AUTHENTICATION_SCHEME is set to AUTHENTICATION_SCHEME_CLIENT_CERTIFICATE one of these properties have to be set :

        • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_KEY_STORE_PASSWORD
        • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD

        No default value.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_KEY_STORE_FORMAT

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PRIVATE_KEY_ALIAS

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PRIVATE_KEY_ALIAS
        String property specifying the private key alias. The alias specifies which private key to use for client authentication in the case where there are more then one private key in the key store. No default value. Can be omitted if the KeyStore only contain one private key.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD
        This property is used to specify the password that deciphers the private key from the key store. When this property is not specified, the private key will be deciphered using the value of the SOLACE_JMS_SSL_KEY_STORE_PASSWORD property instead. This property is required when the private key was encrypted using a different key than the password used to sign the keystore.

        When SOLACE_JMS_AUTHENTICATION_SCHEME is set to AUTHENTICATION_SCHEME_CLIENT_CERTIFICATE one of these properties have to be set :

        • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_KEY_STORE_PASSWORD
        • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD

        No default value.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_SSL_TRUSTED_COMMON_NAME_LIST

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_SSL_TRUSTED_COMMON_NAME_LIST
        String array property specifying a comma separated list of up to 16 acceptable common names for matching in server certificates. The API performs a case insensitive comparison of the common names provided in this property with the common name in the server certificate. Leading and trailing whitespaces are considered to be part of the common names and are not ignored. No common names provided means that all common names are acceptable. No common name validation will be performed (overriding this property) if SOLACE_JMS_SSL_VALIDATE_CERTIFICATE is set to false. Default empty list.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SOLACE_JMS_BROWSER_TIMEOUT_IN_MS

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_BROWSER_TIMEOUT_IN_MS
        Specifies the maximum time in milliseconds for a QueueBrowser Enumeration.hasMoreElements() to wait for a message to arrive in the browser's local message buffer before returning. If there is already a message waiting Enumeration.hasMoreElements() returns immediately. A value of 0 means wait forever ( Enumeration.hasMoreElements() will return false only on closing the browser). A value < 0 will return immediately.

        Default: -1 (return immediately)

        See Also:

      • SOLACE_JMS_GD_RECONNECT_FAIL_ACTION

        static final String SOLACE_JMS_GD_RECONNECT_FAIL_ACTION
        A string property that indicates the behaviour when the API is unable to reconnect guaranteed delivery after reconnecting the session. This may occur if the session is configured with a host list where each Solace router in the host list is unaware of state on the previous router. It can also occur if the time to reconnect to the same router exceeds the publisher flow timeout on the router.

        Default: SupportedProperty.GD_RECONNECT_FAIL_ACTION_AUTO_RETRY
